From: M4 SGLang+MLX Patch Chain
Subject: [PATCH 020] mlx: gemma4 sliding-window (RotatingKVCache) support

Gemma 4's heterogeneous attention layout mixes ContiguousKVCache (full
attention layers) with RotatingKVCache (sliding-window layers, max_size
typically 1024). The MLX batched-decode path had two assumptions that
broke under this layout:

1. `attention_wrapper._batched_decode` called `cache.write_token(k, v)`
   then `cache.get_kv()`. These methods exist only on ContiguousKVCache;
   RotatingKVCache (and every other mlx_lm cache) uses the canonical
   `update_and_fetch(keys, values)` instead. First decode AttributeError'd.

2. After (1) was switched to `update_and_fetch`, `model_runner`'s
   non-hybrid batched path derived a single `seq_lens[i]` per request
   from `caches[i][0].offset`, then assumed ALL layers' K/V would have
   that length after fetch. RotatingKVCache returns at most `max_size`
   (rotating window), so per-request K/V across layers had different
   shapes and `mx.concatenate(axis=0)` ValueErrored:
   shapes `(1,8,7426,256)` vs `(1,8,1024,256)`.

Detected 2026-05-18/19 on gemma4 (26B-A4B MoE) in the MoE-rescue queue.

Fix:

A. `attention_wrapper.py:186` — replace `write_token(k, v)` + `get_kv()`
   with the single `update_and_fetch(keys, values)` call. Works for
   every mlx_lm cache type; behavior unchanged for ContiguousKVCache.

B. `model_runner.py` — both the hybrid batched path (patch 019) and
   the non-hybrid batched path detect `any(isinstance(c, RotatingKVCache)
   for c in caches[0])` and fall back to serial-per-request decode.
   The serial path calls `self.model(input_ids, cache=caches[i])`
   which lets the model's own forward() handle per-layer cache types
   internally (no batched K/V concatenation required).

After this patch gemma4 MoE serves cleanly. Verified 2026-05-19:
4 tool calls (1 glob + 1 read + 2 bash) over 108 s. The model still
doesn't produce an edit — same "engages but can't synthesize" pattern
as qwen35-9b-8bit (model-side ceiling, not stack). See
`evals/swebench/runs/gemma4-moe-mlx-patched-2026-05-19/` for the
post-patch verdict.

Failure class for Gemma 4 MoE upgrades from "MLX backend crash" to
"model synthesis ceiling" — future Gemma 4 variants with better
agentic training would now work through the harness.

